# Performance Rules

## Element Lookups

- Use `elementsMap.get(id)` (O(1) Map lookup) — NEVER `array.find()` or `array.filter()` for element access
- Use `scene.getNonDeletedElementsMap()` for the cached non-deleted elements map
- Use `scene.getElement(id)` which uses the map internally

## Rendering & Throttling

- Static scene rendering is throttled via `renderStaticSceneThrottled` (`throttleRAF`) — do not add additional render calls
- Use `throttleRAF(fn)` from `@excalidraw/common` for any high-frequency callback (pointer moves, scroll, resize)
- Batch React state updates with `withBatchedUpdatesThrottled` from `reactUtils.ts` — combines `unstable_batchedUpdates` + `throttleRAF`
- Never trigger synchronous re-renders from pointer/mouse event handlers

## Cache Invalidation

- Scene mutations automatically bump `sceneNonce` (random integer) — use it as the cache-busting signal
- `Renderer.getRenderableElements()` is memoized and keyed on `sceneNonce` — do not bypass this
- `ShapeCache` uses WeakMap keyed on element references — no manual cleanup needed
- Image cache (`imageCache`) stores loading promises to prevent duplicate fetches

## Memoization

- Use `React.memo` with custom comparators for expensive UI components (see LayerUI pattern)
- Use the project's `memoize()` from `@excalidraw/common` for function-level memoization — not `useMemo` for scene-level caching
- Selected elements are cached with multi-level hashing in `Scene.getSelectedElements()` — do not recompute manually
- `ShapeCache` (WeakMap) caches RoughJS shapes per element — invalidated automatically on mutation

## Event Handlers

- Pointer events use the Emitter pattern (`onPointerDownEmitter`, `onPointerUpEmitter`) — not direct React state updates
- Dynamic event listeners are added on `pointerdown` and removed on `pointerup` — do not add permanent `pointermove` listeners on window
- Store intermediate coordinates in instance variables (`this.lastPointerMoveCoords`), not React state

## Code Splitting & Lazy Loading

- Heavy modules (Mermaid, CodeMirror, font subsetting) are loaded via dynamic `import()` — follow this pattern for new heavy deps
- Use `*.chunk.ts` naming for esbuild split points
- Locale JSON files are lazy-loaded per language code
- Use `WorkerPool` from `packages/excalidraw/workers.ts` for CPU-intensive tasks (auto-manages lifecycle with TTL)

## Forbidden Patterns

- No `array.find(el => el.id === id)` when `elementsMap` is available
- No synchronous heavy computation inside render paths or pointer handlers
- No `setInterval` for animations — use `AnimationFrameHandler` or `AnimationController`
- No permanent `window.addEventListener("pointermove", ...)` — use dynamic add/remove pattern
- No creating new Map/Set/Array on every render — cache or memoize

## How to verify

- `yarn test:app --watch=false` — confirms rendering pipeline performance tests pass
- `grep -rn "\.find(\|\.filter(" packages/excalidraw/renderer/ packages/excalidraw/scene/` — audit for array scans where Map lookup is possible
- `grep -rn "setInterval" packages/excalidraw/` — should only appear in controlled contexts, not for animations
- `grep -rn "addEventListener.*pointermove" packages/excalidraw/components/App.tsx` — verify dynamic add/remove pattern
- Check bundle size: `yarn build:packages` should not significantly increase dist size
